Four people have died and 15 others injured following a crash on the N2 near East London. The crash happened on Monday morning after a driver of a minibus lost control and it overturned. Seven other people died in two separate road crashes in the Eastern Cape over the weekend. Provincial Transport Spokesperson, Unathi Binqose says motorists should exercise caution when using the roads. “We are calling for extra caution on the side of our road users. That’s the message we want to carry out to all those who are on the roads right now to ensure we avoid accidents of this nature. Transport MEC has issued words of condolences to families who’ve lost their loved ones. To those who are recovering in hospital we wish them a speedy recovery.”